      • isPartialInputKey

        boolean isPartialInputKey(java.lang.String raw)
        Determines whether the raw input is a partial prefix of an InputKey. Used to check if sequential additional characters form legal input leading to an InputKey. i.e. if "foo" forms an InputKey, "f" and "fo" and "foo" are all legal and will return true.
        Parameters:
        raw - a raw input String
        Returns:
        true if the input is legal as an initial substring of an InputKey
